===Etymology===
The word is derived with high probability from ''[[dangle]]'', as the device consists of nothing more than a cord and an appendage of no considerable weight, so the whole construction ''dangles''. However, the company called [[w:Rainbow Technologies|Rainbow Technologies]] which manufactured the security dongles back in 1990s claimed that the word comes from the name of its alleged inventor -- Don Gall -- but it's an urban myth. 

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒŋɡəl|-ɒŋɡəl]]

===Noun===
'''dongle'''
# (''Computers''): a hardware device utilised by a specific application for purposes of copy protection. May contain small elements of hardwired application logic. More generally, any short wired connector (such as a network or USB adapter) typically used with a laptop computer.
[[fr:dongle]]

